I create a workspace with n folder today and I ended up with the following workspace file.
```ts
{
	"folders": [
		{
			"path": "jsonrpc"
		},
		{
			"path": "types"
		},
		{
			"path": "protocol"
		},
		{
			"path": "server"
		},
		{
			"path": "client"
		},
		{
			"path": "client.tests"
		}
	],
	"settings": {
		"typescript.tsdk": "./node_modules/typescript/lib",
		"typescript.tsserver.trace": "off",
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterCommaDelimiter": true,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterSemicolonInForStatements": true,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceBeforeAndAfterBinaryOperators": true,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterKeywordsInControlFlowStatements": true,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterFunctionKeywordForAnonymousFunctions": true,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterOpeningAndBeforeClosingNonemptyParenthesis": false,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterOpeningAndBeforeClosingNonemptyBrackets": false,
		"typescript.format.insertSpaceAfterOpeningAndBeforeClosingTemplateStringBraces": false,
		"typescript.format.placeOpenBraceOnNewLineForFunctions": false,
		"typescript.format.placeOpenBraceOnNewLineForControlBlocks": false,
		"javascript.validate.enable": false,
		"eslint.enable": false,
		"tslint.enable": false
	}
}
```

This shows to problems: Typescript didn't mark formatter settings as resource settings. I opened an separate bug for this.

ESlint did the adoption, but I didn't release a new version yet. To avoid polluting the workspace setting section we should be more careful of converting the settings and do the following:

- either let extension flag that they did the adoption by a special flag in the package.json file. If so we convert their settings. If not we leave the settings untouched.
- only convert a setting if it is explicitly marked as window in the package.json. We could still keep the default.

IMO we should address this for September 

//cc @egamma we discussed this 'I did the adoption' flag yesterday.

